For once, a storm is getting a little underhyped. The combo of slow speed, descending trough & high pressure ridge keeping the storm from turning is somewhat unique and really challenges the models.

Until this thing starts turning north, we just won’t know 100%. Danger remains. https://t.co/kUmD902qxR

@MadeByTim @kklausser Expect a substantially wider range of possibilities for this storm than most. We won’t really know what’s happening until the trough and storm align. Change in speed of even 1MPH for the storm would make a very large difference.
